## 🧠 Quick Summary Cheat Sheet

| Question | Simple Answer |
|---|---|
| What is MCP? | A standard language for AI to talk to tools |
| Who made it? | Anthropic (but it's open for anyone to use) |
| What problem does it solve? | Stops everyone from building custom connectors for every AI + tool combo |
| Is it the same as function calling? | Nope! Function calling decides *to* use a tool. MCP is *how* it talks to it |
| Will it become a standard? | Very likely, but not 100% certain yet |
| Should I use it? | If you're building tools for the public — yes! Internally, it depends |

